freshwater: stream near one end of transect
sediment_description: fine sand/mud. Lots of clam shells
general_description: Gradually sloping back of bay. Eelgrass extensive, pits throughout
Notes: internal and external compation number were not given just the compaction itslef. Values reported here are just to make math more to reflect what is written on the data sheet

sediment_description: soft mud with shells intermixed. Changes to sand/mud higher. Cobble outcrops around edge of bay
general_description: Gently sloping beach with lots of eelgrass extending to 0 MLLW

sediment_description: *nothing written on data sheet* WR recalls very muddy changing almost immediately to gravel cobble high
general_description: Very gradual large eelgrass bed. Back of bay with rocky outcrops around with eelgrass inbetween

sediment_description: sand/mud with some shells. Some areas of larger sediments where eelgrass density of a bit lower. Higher shore gravel changing to cobble
general_description: Back of narrow inlet. Bedrock at entrance. Part of bay has fucus patch in mid intertidal

sediment_description: Transect muddy, quickly changes to sand with gravel then to gravel with cobble high
general_description: Moderatly sloped beach along straight section of beach. To right of transect near house more gradual slopping and connect to island the transect is on. Some human debris on beach

sediment_description: muddy. Mud switches to pepple and sand and gravel then gravel high
general_description: Gradually slopping beach back of bay. Eeglrass bed farly narrow. Bounded low by steep drop. Sea otter pits very abundant. Lots of clam shells. One rocky outcrop near center of back of bay. Opposite shore mostly cobble.

sediment_description: muddy sand low at transect changing to gravel high. Cobble at edges of transect
general_description: Relativley small isolated eelgrass bed. Moderatly sloped. Kelp on edges and in deeper subtidal. Eelgrass wasting samples also collected

sediment_description: fine sand/mud changing to gravel and cobble high
general_description: small embayment with eelgrass throuhgout. Moderatly sloped on edges and gradual in back of bay
Notes: internal and external compation number were not given just the compaction itslef. Values reported here are just to make math more to reflect what is written on the data sheet

sediment_description: semi-consolidated sand/mud some shells. One end of transect had cobble on top
general_description: Gradually sloping beach for all of inlet
Notes: 2 crab pot strings were out of water at ~1.5

freshwater: moderate stream off one end of transect
sediment_description: semi-consolidated mud. Lots of clam shells on surface and just below. Turns to sand/mud then cobble high. Two rocky outcrops high
general_description: Fairly linear beach, gradual slope. Lots of clam shell litter

freshwater: small stream plus few tiny streamlets
sediment_description: muddy sand, semi-consolidated shells on top. Lost of shells around -0.3m. Upper shore gradually increases grain size ot gravel and then cobble
general_description: Gradually slopping beach 1 small rock outcrop nob thing in middle of bay at mid intertidal

sediment_description: semi-consolidated sand/mud mix, some small cobbles and shells on top
general_description: Relativley steep beach with eelgrass extenting up to 0 MLLW. Linear

sediment_description: semi-consolidated muddy sand with some gravel in some sections. Changes to sand only with gravel and cobble higher. Scatter rocky outccrops.
general_description: Small crecsent bay with eelgrass. Some eelgrass starts fairly high (above 0 MLLW). Fair amount of algae around more in areas without eelgrass. Water tannins

sediment_description: muddy sand with some gravel mixed in at transect. Changes to gravel and cobble high.
general_description: Small embayment with rocky outcrops on edges. Large stream at one end of transect. Gradual sloping. Visable (while in water) freshwater lense.

sediment_description: soft fine grain sand at transect. Changes to gravel cobble high
general_description: gentle slopping beach with gentle arc. Small island protect most of site

sediment_description: semi-consolidated sand/mud transitioning to cobble
general_description: half moon bay filled with eelgrass. Hard substrate on edges with soft in middle. Flowering shoots present around most of site up to at least 0 MLLW

sediment_description: soft, sink to mid calf, mud, changed to sand/mud then gravel/cobble as you move up the beach
general_description: gradually sloping beach, fairly consistent grade. Start of eeglrass variable but consistent at transect level

freshwater: small stream in back of bay
sediment_description: very soft mud at transect changing to sand/mud then to cobble high
general_description: Long narrow inlet with eelgrass all around. Bed is consistent throughout

sediment_description: sand, gravel, cobble mix. Changes to cobble and gravel high
general_description: Fluvial plain eelgrass throughout, relativlye narrow. About 200m off transect sulfur gas seep in low intertidal, salmon close to transect

sediment_description: muddy sand mixed with gravel and cobble at transect. Changing to course sand with gravel and cobble higher. Two rocky outcrops "framing back of bay
general_description: Gradually slopping beach at back of bay. Lots of shells everywhere that appear old. Eelgrass continuos but some patches rach fairly high i.e. irregraul upper edge

freshwater: many streams in bay, lots of tannins
sediment_description: mostly muddy sand with occasional gravel and sand at transect. Higher becomes more consolidated sand with gravel, cobble and gravel high.
general_description: Large gradual sloping bay with eelgrass throughut. Many streams bisect eelgrass throughout. Eelgrass persists in low elevation stream beds. Its Pete's birthday
